弗兰克·加斯帕罗曾设计过约翰·肯尼迪总统致谢奖章，这次经历也对他设计的半美元背面产生影响。1962年，肯尼迪总统曾指示[[费城铸币局|费城铸币局]]打造300枚致谢奖章，并于1963年6月23日至7月2日访问联邦德国、爱尔兰、英国、意大利和梵蒂冈期间送出。<ref name="Gomez-2015">{{cite book | last = Gomez | first = Darryl A. | year = 2015 | title = Authoritative Numismatist Reference: Presidential Medal of Appreciation Award Medals 1958 - 1963 | publisher = CreateSpace | location = Charleston, SC | isbn = 978-1511786744 | page = 75}}</ref>

富兰克林半美元于1948年面世，但根据[[美国国会|联邦国会]]1890年通过的法案，如果新设计投产不足25年就要再度变更，则必须取得国会授权<ref name="Bardes 1963-12-15" />。1964年12月上旬，来自[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]的[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]][[美国众议院|联邦众议员]][[亨利·B·冈萨雷斯|亨利·冈萨雷斯]]（{{lang|en|Henry Gonzalez}}）提出法案，建议更改半美元硬币设计，刻上肯尼迪总统的肖像<ref name="Bardes 1963-12-08">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1963-12-08 | title = Kennedy issues sought | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 203, Arts & Leisure | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9F01E0D7173FEF3BBC4053DFB4678388679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314154021/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9F01E0D7173FEF3BBC4053DFB4678388679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。12月10日，新总统[[林登·约翰逊|林登·约翰逊]]表态支持发行肯尼迪半美元，请求国会通过适当立法授权从1964年初开始生产新币。约翰逊还称他收到许多赞成这一方案的公众来信，字面行间的情感令他深受感动<ref name="Hunter 1963-12-11">{{cite news | last = Hunter | first = Marjorie | date = 1963-12-11 | title = Coin up to Congress | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 1 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0CE1DD163EE731A25752C1A9649D946291D6CF | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314052219/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0CE1DD163EE731A25752C1A9649D946291D6CF | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。1963年12月30日，国会通过法案授权发行肯尼迪半美元<ref name=Taxay-1983>{{cite book | last = Taxay | first = Don | year = 1983 | origyear = 1966 | title = The U.S. Mint and Coinage | publisher = Sanford J. Durst Numismatic Publications | location = New York | edition = reprint | isbn = 978-0-915262-68-7 | page = 380}}</ref>。铸币局这时已经开始制作模具，由于设计方案快速出台，首批模具得以在1964年1月2日完成<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|138}}。起初铸币局生产的都是[[精制硬币|精制币]]<ref name="Raspus">{{cite web |last=Raspus |first=Ginger |title=Special Mint Set Product of 1960s |url=http://www.numismaster.com/ta/numis/Article.jsp?ad=article&ArticleId=9469 |agency=Numismatic News |website=NumisMaster |date=2010-02-17 |accessdate=2016-02-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130130044159/http://www.numismaster.com/ta/numis/Article.jsp?ad=article&ArticleId=9469 |archivedate=2013-01-30 }}</ref>，首批旨在进入商业流通的肯尼迪半美元是1964年1月30日在[[丹佛铸币局|丹佛铸币局]]铸造，费城铸币局则在1周后投产<ref name="design" />。1964年2月11日，费城和丹佛铸币局举行仪式，庆祝新币正式投产<ref name="Bardes 1964-02-16">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1964-02-16 | title = 'Last word' is issued on Kennedy halves | newspaper = The New York Times | page = X21 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C00E0DD153AE13ABC4E52DFB466838F679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160315022944/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C00E0DD153AE13ABC4E52DFB466838F679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。

== 发行 ==
=== 起初的繁荣 ===
[[File:Eva_Adams_medal.jpeg|thumb]]

在[[美国财政部|财政部]]的安排下，新币于1964年3月24日开始公开发行。人们早早前往财政部位于哥伦比亚特区的硬币销售窗口，排队购买首批公开发售的7万枚半美元。财政部规定每人的购买量不能超过40枚，但当天硬币就销售一空，排出的队伍也并未缩短。位于[[波士顿|波士顿]]和[[费城|费城]]的多间银行很快就开始限制购买量，但所有存币到中午时就已售罄。纽约从次日才开始出售新银币，同样限制每位顾客的购买上限，这令[[金倍尔百货|金倍尔百货]]钱币销售部门的主管人员感到不满，作为纽约市最具实力的钱币经销商，该公司本期望能大批量买下新版半美元，再通过加价销售获利。<ref name="Raymont">{{cite news | last = Raymont | date = 1964-03-25 | title = City banks ration Kennedy 50c coin | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 38 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E01E0DB1138E13ABC4D51DFB566838F679EDE | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314064100/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E01E0DB1138E13ABC4D51DFB566838F679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>

新币在其他国家同样人气高涨。美国[[非洲事务助理国务卿|非洲事务助理国务卿]][[G·门伦·威廉姆斯|G·门伦·威廉姆斯]]（{{lang|en|G. Mennen Williams}}）把用塑料盒包装的半美元送给非洲多个国家的总统和外长，还交给美国驻当地大使，以便他们“为美国在非洲赢得朋友”<ref name="NYT 1964-04-08">{{cite news | date = 1964-04-08 | title = Kennedy coins for Africans | newspaper = The New York Times | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9404EFDA1E3AE13ABC4053DFB266838F679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314041731/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9404EFDA1E3AE13ABC4053DFB266838F679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。硬币公开发行后不久，丹佛铸币局开始接到投诉，称肯尼迪半身像的底部仿佛[[锤子与镰刀|锤子与镰刀]]<ref name="commie">{{cite journal|date=1964-04-17 |title=People: Apr. 17, 1964 |journal=Time |accessdate=2016-02-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140324231929/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C875809-2%2C00.html |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,875809-2,00.html |archivedate=2014-03-24 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。罗伯茨对此回应称，这实际上不过是他的姓名首字母缩写“{{lang|en|<small>GR</small>}}”的花押字<ref name="commie" />。

为满足巨大的市场需求，铸币局大量生产肯尼迪半美元。财政部原计划在1964年发行9100万枚半美元，之后又提升到1.41亿枚。但是，公开宣布加大发行量之举并未令实际商品流通中的半美元增多，也没有促使二级市场中倒卖半美元的价格下滑。<ref name="Bardes 1964-07-19">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1964-07-19 | title = Uncertainties follow Treasury proposals | newspaper = The New York Times | page = X17 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0CE0D9153DEF32A2575AC1A9619C946591D6CF | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160315091006/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0CE0D9153DEF32A2575AC1A9619C946591D6CF | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>到11月下旬时，铸币局已经打造约1.6亿枚新币，但市场流通中仍难见其身影。白银价格逐渐升高，令大量硬币被囤积起来<ref name="Bardes 1964-11-22">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1964-11-22 | title = Turmoil in the Capital | newspaper = The New York Times | page = X26 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9902E0D7123DEE3ABC4A51DFB767838F679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313084754/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9902E0D7123DEE3ABC4A51DFB767838F679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。为了发行更多刻有1964年份的硬币，打击投机炒作行径，财政部请求国会授权，在进入1965年后继续生产所刻年份为1964的半美元并获得批准<ref name="Bardes 1964-07-19" /><ref name="Bardes 1964-09-13">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1964-09-13 | title = Treasury to go ahead on '64 date freeze | newspaper = The New York Times | page = X32 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=950CEED7123AE13ABC4B52DFBF66838F679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306103447/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=950CEED7123AE13ABC4B52DFBF66838F679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。最终标称年份为1964的肯尼迪半美元共生产了约4.3亿枚，比过去16年间生产的富兰克林半美元流通币总和还多<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|138}}。

大量出产银币导致财政部的白银库存迅速减少，银价随即飞速上涨，到1965年6月上旬时，单枚5美分硬币中包含白银的市场价格竟然达到9.33美分。1965年6月3日，约翰逊总统宣布计划不再在5美分和25美分硬币中采用银，改用纯铜内芯，外面再以铜镍合金包裹，半美元的材质组成也经调整，含银量从90%大幅调低至40%<ref name="Dale">{{cite news | last = Dale | first = Edwin L. Jr. | date = 1965-06-04 | title = President asks quarters and dimes without silver | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 1 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E02E4DA163BE13ABC4C53DFB066838E679EDE | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314162525/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E02E4DA163BE13ABC4C53DFB066838E679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。同年7月，国会通过《[[1965年铸币法案|1965年铸币法案]]》<ref name="NYT 1965-07-15">{{cite news | title = Coin bill approved by Senate and sent to the White House | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 1965-07-15 | agency = AP | page = 1 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9A03EED9133CE733A25755C1A9619C946491D6CF | archive-date = 2016-03-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313143524/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9A03EED9133CE733A25755C1A9619C946491D6CF | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。新半美元仍然保留银色外观，外层合金采用80%的银和20%的铜，内层则是21%的银和79%的铜。首批包覆式半美元于1965年12月30日在丹佛铸币局生产，上面附有年份1965，并且这种年份会一直生产到硬币短缺情况缓解之后<ref name="NYT 1965-12-30">{{cite news | title = Minting of New Half Dollar To Begin Today in Denver - Article - NYTimes.com | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 1965-12-30 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0DE5DD1430E33ABC4850DFB467838E679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-02-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160216220701/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0DE5DD1430E33ABC4850DFB467838E679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。铸币局从1966年8月1日开始打造刻有年份1966的半美元，并从这时开始恢复以往惯例，硬币所标称的年份就是其生产年份。虽然政府宣称硬币已不再短缺<ref name="Bardes 1966-07-17">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1966-07-17 | title = 1966 date begins Aug. 1 | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 96 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0DE1D81531E43BBC4F52DFB166838D679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-04-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160423215802/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C0DE1D81531E43BBC4F52DFB166838D679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>，但在囤积持续和产量回落的共同影响下，肯尼迪半美元在市场流通中仍然难得一见，而且财政部也不愿把白银储备更快地消耗在不流通的硬币上<ref name="NYT 1969-02-09">{{cite news | date = 1969-02-09 | title = The half-dollar growing scarcer | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 92 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990CE1DC133BE73ABC4153DFB4668382679EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-04-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160413135209/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990CE1DC133BE73ABC4153DFB4668382679EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。钱币学作家兼经销商[[昆汀·戴维·鲍尔斯|昆汀·戴维·鲍尔斯]]（{{lang|en|Q. David Bowers}}）对此表示：

{{quote
| 时至今日，数以千万计的（肯尼迪半美元）依然不知所踪。与此同时，自1932年起就没有变更过设计的[[华盛顿25美分硬币|华盛顿25美分硬币]]成为流通量最大的几种硬币中面额最高的一种，在自动贩卖机、街机游戏等同类性质商品交易中特别流行。这种情况一直持续到现在，无论是肯尼迪半美元，还是后来发行的其他面额不超一美元的硬币，几乎都从来没有在市场流通中出现。<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|vi}}
}}

=== 改用贱金属材质 ===
{{for|1975至1976年间出产的流通版纪念一美元、半美元和25美分硬币|美国二百周年纪念币}}
1969年5月，财政部请求国会授权，将半美元的材质组成改成和五美分、25美分硬币相同的铜镍合金，不再包含白银。财政部同时还希望国会同意以贱金属铸造一美元面额硬币，用来满足[[美国西部|西部]]赌场对游戏代币的需求。前总统[[德怀特·艾森豪威尔|德怀特·艾森豪威尔]]此时去世未久，部分政府官员提议在一美元硬币上刻上艾森豪威尔的肖像。财政部希望通过取消硬币中的银，促使人们不再囤积，恢复半美元和一美元硬币的市场流通。<ref name="UPI 1969-05-13">{{cite news | title = End of silver use in U.S. coins urged | date = 1969-05-13 | agency = United Press International | newspaper = The Press–Courier | location = Oxnard, California | page = 6 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=XRJSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=pzQNAAAAIBAJ&dq=kennedy%20half%20dollar&pg=6091%2C2616341 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2020-02-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200207171605/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=XRJSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=pzQNAAAAIBAJ&dq=kennedy%20half%20dollar&pg=6091%2C2616341 | dead-url = no }}</ref>财政部的提议得到[[理查德·尼克松|理查德·尼克松]]总统支持，但部分共和党联邦众议员对把艾森豪威尔放在[[贱金属|贱金属]]硬币上感到不满，所以反对提案<ref name="Hunt">{{cite news | last = Hunt | first = Robert A. | date = 1969-10-07 | title = Ike Dollar Plan Halted | agency = Associated Press | newspaper = Waycross Journal-Herald | location = Waycross, Georgia | page = 1 | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=J2FjAAAAIBAJ&sjid=qkoNAAAAIBAJ&dq=kennedy%20half%20dollar&pg=4323%2C504946 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2020-02-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200229232914/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=J2FjAAAAIBAJ&sjid=qkoNAAAAIBAJ&dq=kennedy%20half%20dollar&pg=4323%2C504946 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。经过一年多的拉锯战，尼克松于1970年12月31日签署法案授权发行[[艾森豪威尔一美元硬币|艾森豪威尔一美元硬币]]，并取消半美元硬币材质中采用的银<ref name="Haney">{{cite news | last = Haney | first = Thomas V. | date = 1971-01-24 | title = Ike dollar to be last silver coin | newspaper = The New York Times | page = D29 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D03EEDC103BE73ABC4C51DFB766838A669EDE | archive-date = 2016-03-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160306105828/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9D03EEDC103BE73ABC4C51DFB766838A669EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。受这1年多拖延的影响，除精制币外的1970年版肯尼迪半美元只在丹佛铸币局生产，并且只通过铸币局套装发行。这种1970-{{lang|en|D}}版半美元总产量只有210万枚，是全系列中最少的品种，不过这一数量仍然足以保持其价格不会过高。铸币局一直等到停止接受硬币套装订单后才宣布不会生产流通用1970年版半美元<ref name="Green">{{cite web | last = Green | first = Paul M. | date = 2010-10-04 | title = 1970-D Kennedy remains volatile | website = Numismatic News | url = http://www.numismaticnews.net/article/1970_d_kennedy_remains_volatile | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150428043308/http://www.numismaticnews.net/article/1970_d_kennedy_remains_volatile | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-04-28}}</ref>。

半美元至此不再采用白银，但却已淡出市场流通太久，许多银行已经没有再在机器上提供这种面额的卡槽。铸币局虽预计半美元的订单会卷土重来，<ref name="Free Lance–Star 1971-12-15">{{cite news | newspaper = The Free Lance–Star | date = 1971-12-15 | title = New silverless dollar; half dollar to return | location = Fredericksburg, Virginia | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zuVNAAAAIBAJ&sjid=c4oDAAAAIBAJ&dq=eisenhower%20dollar%20half%20dollar%20silver&pg=7189%2C5672297 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | page = 4 | archive-date = 2020-02-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200207171058/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zuVNAAAAIBAJ&sjid=c4oDAAAAIBAJ&dq=eisenhower%20dollar%20half%20dollar%20silver&pg=7189%2C5672297 | dead-url = no }}</ref>但局长[[玛丽·布鲁克斯|玛丽·布鲁克斯]]（{{lang|en|Mary Brooks}}）于1971年7月透露，财政部已库存两亿枚贱金属半美元新币，商业银行也没有多少兴趣下单。“我真是不明白，人们为啥就是不用它们（指半美元硬币）。”<ref name="Neikirk">{{cite news | last = Neikirk | first = Bill | date = 1971-07-28 | title = Half dollars gathering dust | agency = Associated Press | newspaper = Kentucky New Era | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-vErAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HAYGAAAAIBAJ&pg=894%2C2484364 | page = 13 | location = Hopkinsville, Kentucky | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2021-04-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210419223809/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-vErAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HAYGAAAAIBAJ&pg=894%2C2484364 | dead-url = no }}</ref>据布鲁克斯所言，含银的肯尼迪半美元总产量超过10亿枚，其中绝大多数被公众囤积。对此她的解释是，含银的肯尼迪半美元流通率极低，同时1970年时铸币局又因预计国会将授权材质变更而只生产很少的半美元硬币，这导致公众已经习惯于商品交易中没有半美元的身影。布鲁克斯还认为：“如果举国上下都知道还有大量半美元存在，他们或许也会将之囤积起来。”<ref name="Neikirk" />

1973年3月5日，布鲁克斯宣布铸币局会向社会征集25美分、半美元和一美元硬币的[[美国二百周年纪念币|新版背面设计方案]]，为1976年的美国独立200周年准备纪念币<ref name="NYT 1973-03-05">{{cite news | date = 1973-03-05 | title = Coins to get new look for 1976 celebration | newspaper = The New York Times | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990CE6DF1430E63ABC4E53DFB5668388669EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313015139/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=990CE6DF1430E63ABC4E53DFB5668388669EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。10月18日，尼克松总统签署第93-127号公共法案，批准为3种面额硬币物色新设计，设计方案需切合200周年纪念的主题。铸币局宣布通过竞赛选拔方案，任何美国公民都可以递交作品参赛<ref name="US Mint timeline">{{cite web | title = Timeline of the United States Mint | accessdate = 2014-11-29 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129145046/http://www.usmint.gov/historianscorner/?action=timeline&century=1900 | url = http://www.usmint.gov/historianscorner/?action=timeline&century=1900 | publisher = United States Mint | archivedate = 2014-11-29}}</ref>。最终塞斯·亨廷顿（{{lang|en|Seth G. Huntington}}）的[[美国独立纪念馆|独立厅]]主题设计获选成为半美元的背面<ref name="Bardes 1974-08-25">{{cite news | last = Bardes | first = Herbert C. | date = 1974-08-25 | title = Bicentennial coins make debut | newspaper = The New York Times | page = 26, Arts & Leisure | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9405E2DE1E3BE53ABC4D51DFBE66838F669EDE | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160312140511/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9405E2DE1E3BE53ABC4D51DFBE66838F669EDE | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。1975和1976年生产的肯尼迪半美元背面承载的都是亨廷顿的设计方案，并且正面的年份改为“1776–1976”，代表[[美国独立宣言|独立宣言]]签署暨美国独立200周年<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|155–156}}。最终出产的200周年纪念半美元超过5.21亿枚<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|270}}。

虽然200周年纪念币的产量甚高，但肯尼迪半美元的产量此后逐年下降。1979年，铸币局局长斯特拉·黑克尔（{{lang|en|Stella B. Hackel}}）透露铸币局会继续生产这种硬币。“我们觉得用于商品流通的半美元的确不多，但这些硬币总还是流到了什么地方，所以肯定还是有人需要它们。”<ref name="Reiter 1979-08-19">{{cite news | last = Reiter | first = Ed | date = 1979-08-19 | title = Kennedy half dollars are still in demand | newspaper = The New York Times | page = D35, Arts & Leisure | url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C05E3D71E38E732A2575AC1A96E9C946890D6CF | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archive-date = 2016-03-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160314235411/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C05E3D71E38E732A2575AC1A96E9C946890D6CF | dead-url = no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。肯尼迪半美元的总产量这时已突破25亿枚，超过之前每种半美元的产量总和。《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》钱币专栏作家埃德·瑞特（{{lang|en|Ed Reiter}}）指出，即便材质组成完全只有贱金属，也没能阻止人们继续囤积肯尼迪半美元，导致商品交易中这种硬币难得一见。<ref name="Reiter 1979-08-19" />受高银价的影响，20世纪70年代下半叶有大量早期肯尼迪半美元被熔融，以取得其中的白银来获利<ref name="cw">{{cite news | title = Kennedy half dollar instantly popular with collectors | work = Coin World | archivedate = 2010-12-15 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101215135906/http://coinworld.com/NewCollector/AboutUSCoins/HalfDollar_Kennedy.aspx | url = http://www.coinworld.com/NewCollector/AboutUSCoins/HalfDollar_Kennedy.aspx | accessdate = 2010-12-15 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>。

20世纪剩下的20多年里，铸币局继续生产半美元，产量在费城和丹佛铸币局都基本保持稳定<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|270–271}}，这其中只有1987年例外，铸币局这年没有生产流通用半美元硬币，因为财政部已有足够维持供应两年的存量，没有持续生产的必要<ref name="Richterman">{{cite news | last = Richterman | first = Anita | date = 1987-06-23 | title = Problem line | newspaper = Newsday | page = 21}} {{subscription}}</ref>。半美元一度在赌场中流行，但因为许多赌场开始采用50美分代币，半美元的市场需求旋即下跌<ref name=Lange-2006>{{cite book | last = Lange | first = David W. | year = 2006 | title = History of the United States Mint and its Coinage | url = https://archive.org/details/historyofuniteds0000lang | publisher = Whitman Publishing | location = Atlanta | isbn = 978-0-7948-1972-9 | page = [https://archive.org/details/historyofuniteds0000lang/page/174 174]}}</ref>。由于产量多年不见提升<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|270–271}}，铸币局从2002年开始不再生产用于商务流通的肯尼迪半美元。人们可以在铸币局购买现年版本的袋装硬币，但价格要高于面值<ref name="cw" />。

[[File:Kennedy_line_1.jpg|thumb]]

2014年1月，某私营公司应铸币局之请开展调查，了解人们是否会对肯尼迪半美元面世50周年之际发行特别版感兴趣<ref name="cw2014">{{cite news | last = Gilkes | first = Paul | title = Gold Kennedy half dollar in collectors' future? | work = Coin World | url = http://www.coinworld.com/articles/gold-kennedy-half-dollar-in-collectors-future | archivedate = 2014-03-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140302153347/http://www.coinworld.com/articles/gold-kennedy-half-dollar-in-collectors-future | date = 2014-02-24 | accessdate = 2014-03-02 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>。同年6月，铸币局宣布计划发行七种2014年特别版肯尼迪半美元，纪念该系列硬币50周年，其中两种采用合金包覆，分别由费城和丹佛铸币局生产；四种为银币，分别由费城、丹佛、[[旧金山铸币局|旧金山]]和[[西点铸币局|西点铸币局]]生产；还有一种是金币，纯度为99.99%，由西点铸币局打造。合金和银币版所刻年份为2014，金币版则是代表50周年的“1964–2014”。全部7种特别版的浮雕都比原本发行的普通版本高<ref name="cw2014a">{{cite news | last = Gilkes | first = Paul | title = United States Mint planning to release seven 50th anniversary Kennedy half dollars in 2014 | work = Coin World | date = 2014-06-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150118035240/http://www.coinworld.com/news/united-states-mint-planning-seven-50th-anniversary-kennedy-half-.html | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archivedate = 2015-01-18 | url = https://www.coinworld.com/news/us-coins/2014/06/united-states-mint-planning-seven-50th-anniversary-kennedy-half-.html}}</ref>。2014年8月5日，[[美国钱币协会|美国钱币协会]]在[[伊利诺伊州|伊利诺伊州]][[库克县_(伊利诺伊州)|库克县]]的[[罗斯蒙特_(伊利诺伊州)|罗斯蒙特]]（{{lang|en|Rosemont}}）召开大会，金质肯尼迪半美元就在会上发布<ref name="cw2014c">{{cite news | last = Roach | first = Steve | title = Lots of winners for new 1964—2014 gold Kennedy half dollar | work = Coin World | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150906194901/http://www.coinworld.com/voices/steve-roach/2014/08/lots_of_winners_for.html | url = https://www.coinworld.com/voices/steve-roach/2014/08/lots_of_winners_for.html | date = 2014-08-05 | accessdate = 2016-02-11 | archivedate = 2015-09-06 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

== 收藏 ==
[[File:Kennedy-Half-Dollar-Accented-Hair.jpg|thumb]]
除1965至1967年外，铸币局每年都有生产精制币，其材质与普遍币相同<ref name="1976silver">{{cite web | title = First Strikes Celebrate the Bicentennial press release | publisher = United States Mint | archivedate = 2013-05-29 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130529071936/http://www.usmint.gov/historianscorner/?action=DocDL&doc=pr487.pdf | url = http://www.usmint.gov/historianscorner/?action=DocDL&doc=pr487.pdf | accessdate = 2013-05-29 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>。首批肯尼迪半美元精制币于1964年1月上旬铸造。面世最早的约10万枚精制币正面人物肖像的头发线条很粗，经过修改，之后出产的近400万枚精制币没有这一特征。<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|248}}受硬币短缺影响，财政部宣布1965年不会生产精制币套装<ref name="Raspus" />。但为满足收藏家的需求还是有打造铸币局特制套装。这些套装包含的硬币是1966年初在[[旧金山铸币局|旧金山化验办事处]]铸造，采用经过重度抛光处理的1965年版模具，上面没有铸造标记。<ref name="Raspus" />此后铸币局还有生产带1966和1967年份数字的类似套装<ref name="Yeoman-2014">{{cite book | last = Yeoman | first = R.S. | year = 2014 | title = A Guide Book of United States Coins | url = https://archive.org/details/guidebookofunite0068yeom | edition = 68th | publisher = Whitman Publishing | location = Atlanta | isbn = 978-0-7948-4215-4}}</ref>{{rp|353–354}}。铸币局特制套装中有少量半美元背面没有加斯帕罗的姓名首字母缩写花押字“{{lang|en|<small>FG</small>}}”，这显然是因模具抛光过度所致<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|244}}。1964年出产的精制币是装在软塑料盒内出售，1966和1967年版套装则是以超声波焊接密封在硬塑料盒中<ref name="Yeoman-2014" />{{rp|353–354}}。1968年，铸币局恢复常规精制币生产<ref name="Yeoman-2014" />{{rp|348–351}}，只不过生产任务移交旧金山铸币局，硬币上因此加上铸造标记“{{lang|en|S}}”，以硬质塑料盒封装后成套出售<ref name="Tomaska-2011" />{{rp|248}}。

1973年，国会授权铸币局为收藏家打造银质包覆层的200周年纪念版肯尼迪半美元，铸币局于1975年4月开始生产<ref name="1976silver" />。之后发行的版本包括精制币和未流通版两种品相。1975和1976年精制币套装中还有铜镍合金包覆层的200周年纪念版半美元，并同银质包覆层版一起按三枚一套出售<ref name="Yeoman-2014" />{{rp|212–213}}。铸币局从1992年开始以90%的含银量为银质精制币特别套装铸造肯尼迪半美元。1964年的精制币是在费城打造，但从1968年起就只有旧金山铸币局生产。<ref name="Yeoman-2014" />{{rp|212–214}}1998年，铸币局生产了部分哑光工艺银质半美元精制币，与纪念[[罗伯特·F·肯尼迪遇刺案|同样遇刺]]的罗伯特·肯尼迪的[[纪念币|纪念]]一美元硬币一起作为套装出售<ref name="Sanders">{{cite journal | last = Sanders | first = Mitch | date = 2007-09 | title = Collecting Kennedy Halves | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140323121929/https://www.money.org/media/10403/KennedyHalves.pdf | deadurl = yes | journal = Numismatist | page = 114 | url = https://www.money.org/media/10403/KennedyHalves.pdf | accessdate = 2014-03-23 | archivedate = 2014-03-23}}</ref>。2005至2010年间，铸币局套装中的未流通品相半美元表面呈哑光处理效果，以同装袋销售的精制币相区别<ref name="cw" />。

